ingenic_adc_aux: add 'invert' module param to flip inverted-polarity sensors

Some boards (e.g. this DML16-Z533 T41NQ) wire the day/night photoresistor so
that bright light gives a LOW value and darkness gives a HIGH value - the
inverse of what consumers expect. raptor's RIC day/night reads AUX0 assuming
higher = brighter and has no invert option, so with an inverted LDR it never
switches (measured: bright = 0, darkest = ~14997 of a ~17995 full scale).

Add a module parameter 'invert': a reference ceiling. When non-zero the value
returned to userspace becomes (invert - reading), clamped at 0 to avoid
underflow. Applied to the final (scaled) value RIC reads, so tuning is
intuitive: pick invert slightly above full scale (e.g. 20000) and bright->high,
dark->low. Evaluated per sample, so runtime writable via
/sys/module/ingenic_adc_aux/parameters/invert . Default 0 = unchanged.

Enable with ingenic_adc_aux.invert=20000 on the kernel cmdline, or echo it at
runtime. Only AUX0 (the LDR) is consumed for day/night on this board.

Signed-off-by: Oskari Rauta <oskari.rauta@gmail.com>

--- a/drivers/mfd/ingenic_adc_aux.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/ingenic_adc_aux.c
@@ -33,6 +33,14 @@
 
 static unsigned long int VREF_ADC = 1800;
 
+/* Inverted-polarity sensor support: when non-zero, the value returned to
+ * userspace becomes (invert - reading), clamped at 0. For a photoresistor wired
+ * bright=low / dark=high, set invert slightly above full scale (e.g. 20000) so
+ * bright->high, dark->low as raptor RIC day/night expects. 0 = disabled. */
+static unsigned int invert = 0;
+module_param(invert, uint, 0644);
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(invert, "reference ceiling; returned value = invert - reading (0 = disabled), e.g. 20000");
+
 #define AUXCONST   4096
 
 #define ADC_MAGIC_NUMBER	'A'
@@ -148,6 +156,8 @@
 	ingenic_adc_aux->cell->disable(ingenic_adc_aux->pdev);
 
 	sadc_volt = sadc_volt * VREF_ADC*10 / AUXCONST;
+	if (invert)
+		sadc_volt = (sadc_volt < invert) ? (invert - sadc_volt) : 0;
 
 	return sadc_volt;
 }
